        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 24 at 3:27PM EDT until June 24 at 3:45PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 327 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Royal Oak, or
near Warren, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

This severe storm will be near...
Troy around 330 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this severe thunderstorm include
Rochester Hills, Franklin, Madison Heights, Clawson, Berkley, Oak
Park, Hazel Park, Lathrup Village, Bingham Farms, and Bloomfield
Hills.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
